      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Hey {first_name, \"there\"},</p><p>Back when I was training journalists to blog, I used to describe one form of blogging as ‚Äúlike keeping your notebook in public‚Äù. It's just dawned on me that that's exactly what these Tuesday and Thursday newsletters are ‚Äî a compilation of interesting things that have crossed my desk. Well, my metaphorical desk; my wife is curretly occupying my actual, physical desk, as she lectures to medical genetics students‚Ä¶</p><p>Five and done today, with a focus on online community tools. We're going to need online communities in the coming months, as many places start clamping down on face to face meetings again. üò∑</p>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Local journalists under sustained online attack",
            "type": "text",
