      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "src": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1495558685573-aba7573d9c01?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&q=80&fm=jpg&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&w=2000&fit=max&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjExNzczfQ",
        "width": 3000,
        "height": 2053,
        "caption": "Photo by <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/@whoislimos?utm_source=ghost&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api-credit\">whoislimos</a> / <a href=\"https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=ghost&utm_medium=referral&utm_campaign=api-credit\">Unsplash</a>",
        "alt": "In despair, but not lost. I try to remind myself, trials may come yet hope lies at dawn"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "New research highlights the depressing amount of abuse local journalists face:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The most common platform for abuse is Facebook, with 89% of respondents receiving abuse on this platform. For Twitter, it‚Äôs 67%. Eighty per cent say they receive abuse in the comments sections of their newspaper websites.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "quote",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Three thoughts:",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "The fact that Facebook is the biggest problem should dispell the old myth that doing away with anonymity woule resolve trolling problems",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
            "value": 1,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "As ever, don't have a comment section if you're not prepared to manage it. (Drive-by politcial abuse is one of the reasons I've restriced commenting here to signed-in subscribers. Try it! ‚¨áÔ∏è)",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "listitem",
            "value": 2,
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "I remain concerned that, as local journalists become ever more distant from the communities they serve, this is only going to get worse. ",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
